data.content:
After investigating how the @NASA_Orion spacecrafts heat shield fared during the Artemis I mission to the Moon, we are confidently preparing for Artemis II with the heat shield already attached to the capsule.
 
#Artemis II is now targeted for April 2026. https://t.co/o1i0nxU9VQ https://t.co/uNQFeWNwm2

LIVE: NASA leadership is providing an update on our @NASAArtemis campaign, which will explore the Moon for scientific discoveries, economic benefits, and lessons learned for crewed missions to Mars. https://t.co/9VBGQ9YjmG

Tonight, Vega-C  is returning to flight.

Launch chronology has restarted at Europe's Spaceport in French Guiana and our rocket is set to carry @CopernicusEU #Sentinel1 C to space.

 Liftoff targeted for 21:20 GMT/22:20 CET.

 Tune in from 21:00 GMT/22:00 CET on https://t.co/JUgZA26d1j

We have a mission!  
 
Learn more about the mission from the Proba-3 team as they bid farewell to their satellite, while ESA's Director General, @AschbacherJosef, wishes the team the best of luck.
 
Go Proba-3! https://t.co/JwNJNFQggt

Proba-3 successfully lifted off from Satish Dhawan Space Centre on @isro's PSLV-XL on 5 December 2024.

The double-satellite is the most ambitious member yet of our Proba family of experimental missions. Two spacecraft will fly together as one, maintaining precise formation down https://t.co/WKwFdyQ6CK
LIFTOFF of #Proba3 on PSLV-XL rocket from Satish Dhawan Space Centre in Sriharikota, India a on 5 December 2024! https://t.co/wyT53jzAkn
Live now: coverage has started for the launch of our Proba-3 mission on a PSLV-XL rocket from Satish Dhawan Space Centre in Sriharikota, India  https://t.co/cPbPMCWZ39

Our eclipse-making Proba-3 mission is set for launch! 
  
  Liftoff is scheduled for TODAY at 10:34 GMT/11:34 CET. 
  Join us live from 10:00 GMT/11:00 CET  https://t.co/cPbPMCWZ39 

Learn more about the mission  https://t.co/3zCG5T1z0R https://t.co/IFyVEfyHCJ

NASA provided an update on the Artemis campaign today, including a new launch date for CSA astronaut @astro_Jeremy Hansen and the Artemis II crew. Read the statement from CSA President Lisa Campbell. https://t.co/ydxcbs2hJ4 https://t.co/qZjwUxWTgj
